				\begin{document}$${Q}_{e}=\rho {C}_{P}\frac{\delta T}{\delta t}-{\nabla }(K\ast {\nabla }T)$$\end{document}Qe=ρCPδTδt−∇(K∗∇T)where ρ is density [g/cm3], CP is the specific heat capacity at constant pressure [J/g.K], K is thermal conductivity [W/cm.K] and ∇T is the temperature gradient [K/cm] along the longitudinal profile of the sample model.
